Here's a comprehensive list of Terraform components, organized by category.
Core Language Blocks (HCL)

terraform — settings block (required_version, required_providers, backend, cloud)
provider — configure a provider (AWS, Azure, GCP, etc.)
resource — manage an infrastructure object
data — data source (read-only lookup)
variable — input variable
output — output value
locals — local values (computed expressions)
module — call a reusable module
moved — refactor/track resource address changes
import (block) — declarative import (1.5+)
removed — declare removal without destroy (1.7+)
check — post-apply assertions (1.5+)

State Management

State file (terraform.tfstate)
Backends (local, s3, azurerm, gcs, consul, http, kubernetes, etc.)
State locking (DynamoDB, blob lease, etc.)
Remote state (terraform_remote_state data source)
Workspaces (state isolation)

